# Library Provider Rules (`Services/Library/`)

Discovery/browse only — Library NEVER writes to the bookmark tree; no bookmark-creation or release-watcher subsystem. Read-only outbound HTTP to public catalogs; no credentials stored for these sites. Full spec: `Docs/library-phases.md`.

## Provider abstraction

All providers implement `IMediaProvider` — one provider's outage or removal never blocks the others. Track success/failure metrics, request budget/cache hits; provider toggles via AppConfig.

## Per-provider constraints

- **AniList, MangaDex, Kitsu, RanobeDB** — public APIs. RanobeDB covers Japanese light novels (official releases) only, NOT raw web novels.
- **Novelfire** — raw/fan-translated web novels, **bulk-catalog-only**: robots.txt disallows `/search?keyword=*` and `/api/*`. Never implement live search against those endpoints; only genre-listing/novel-detail crawling (allowed).
- **RoyalRoad** — never bulk-import (no bulk API, scraping ToS risk); search-time-only.

## Catalog crawl

Populate `LibraryCatalogEntry` (Browse view source) only from providers implementing `IBulkCatalogProvider`. Drive the crawl exclusively off the durable `LibraryCatalogSyncQueueItem` table (Queue-Based Load Leveling), never in-memory state — restart mid-crawl must resume without loss.

## Titles

Prefer English title when provider exposes localized titles (AniList `title.english`, Kitsu `titles.en`); fall back to native/romanized only when no English title exists.
